title: International Comprehensive Ocean-Atmosphere Data Set
comment: The ICOADS contains O(500M) meteorological observations from ~1650 onwards. Issues include bad observation values, mis-positioned data, missing date/time information, supplemental data in a variety of formats, duplicates etc., recursive download

title: London Air
comment: Lots of gaps (null/zero handling), outliers, date handling, pivots and time aggregation needed first! Web scraping

title: The Metropolitan Museum of Art Open Access
comment: Missing values, inconsistent information, missing documentation, possible duplication, mixed text and numeric data.

title: Flourish OA
comment: Scraped data, has some missing fields, possible duplication and some encoding issues (possibly multiple character encodings).

title: Register of UK Parliament Members’ Financial Interests
comment:
single year is enough 
 Each member’s transactions are on a separate webpage with a different text format, with contributions listed under different headings (not necessarily one per line) and in different formats. Will take quite a bit of careful preprocessing to get into CSV or JSON format. 
 HELP: https://github.com/benscott/mp-financial-interests

title: Hourly Weather Surface – Brazil (Southeast region)
comment: Can you predict the amount of rain? Temperature? NOTE: Not all weather stations started operating since 2000

title: World Development Indicators
comment: intensive extrapolation and visualization. Inspiration from kaggle kernels is available. This means though that your results should be even more stunning

title: IRS
comment: free text form. you do not need to download it completely. 100 MB are enough

title: UCI KDD98
comment: synthetically genreate noise (missing values, wrong data type) and then try to clean it up again

title: Kaggle
comment: No nulls, but outliers and bad data are still hidden

title: USA Voting prediction
comment: Alternatively choose Austria or Germany or another country. But then make sure that you quickly find a source where to get the data from. Other wise choose adifferent dataset

title: catholy nuns survey 1967: predict age based on religious beliefs
Propose your own
comment: If you have your own dataset, feel free to propose it, but make sure that you already know where to get it from. Otherwise choose one of the suggested ones.
